			<div class="content">It will all end in tears.<br />or in hyperinflation.<br />Whichever comes first.<br /><br />And yes, thanks to the voting the USA is now effectively ruled by Goldman Sachs and whoever they managed to get appointed to the whitehouse to protect their financial interests in this year's president's cabinet. They are basically attempting to inflate their way out of trouble, but since they do not adress the underlying causes of the economic problems and there is nobody with the political clout to make sure something gets done (both parties have been told by the voters that no matter the bipartisan rhetoric they claim to want they will actually reward those who refuse to even cooperate with the other part), this printing of 600 billions of dollars will do nothing in even the short run. The money will simply leave the country in search of more profitable economies, until such time as the rest of the world is fed up with this tactic and stops accepting dollars so readily. At that point the American economy ceases to be the world economy and will end up having hundreds times as much money in roulation as it has economy to use it on.<br /><br /><br />Eri</div>

			

